      {
        "id": "msg-1",
        "role": "user",
        "type": "text",
        "content": "I own 3 properties, QLD (worth 600k and 80% LVR), Vic (worth $920k and 100% LVR) & NT ($500k with 80% LVR). My goal is to retire by 2046 on $250k cash flow. I am interested in buying a commercial property with a 6% yield to help me get there quicker. I am also interested in buildinga granny flat on my Vic house for $180k.",
        "timestamp": 1782703844211
      },
      {
        "id": "msg-3",
        "role": "assistant",
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Great context \u2014 a few things I need before I can model this out.\n\n**Income & savings**\n- What is your annual income (or combined income if you have a partner)?\n- How much are you saving each month?\n\n**Existing properties \u2014 loan details**\n- QLD property: what is the current loan balance?\n- VIC property: what is the current loan balance?\n- NT property: what is the current loan balance?\n\n**Deposit / cash available**\n- How much cash do you have available for new purchases (outside of equity)?\n\n**Commercial property**\n- Do you have a target price in mind, or a location/state preference?\n\n**Granny flat**\n- Is the $180k granny flat build funded from cash savings, or are you looking to draw equity from the VIC property to fund it?\n\nOnce I have those, I can build the full plan including the commercial purchase and granny flat scenario.",
        "timestamp": 1782703854237
      },
      {
        "id": "msg-4",
        "role": "user",
        "type": "text",
        "content": "income - $250k, saving s- $300k",
